00:05:22,073 --> 00:05:23,074
Because it's really interesting.

101
00:05:23,955 --> 00:05:31,004
The first game that was actually accused of stealing was no other than Atari's game Pong.

102
00:05:32,053 --> 00:05:34,995
Many people think that Pong was the first game actually in history,

103
00:05:35,415 --> 00:05:40,038
but it turns out that a console called the Magnavox Odyssey

104
00:05:40,398 --> 00:05:43,520
released a game called Tennis two years before Pong.

105
00:05:44,141 --> 00:05:46,542
So they threatened to sue Atari and take them to court,

106
00:05:47,182 --> 00:05:50,484
and Atari settled outside court, licensed the game,

107
00:05:50,825 --> 00:05:52,586
and released Pong, and the rest is history.

108
00:05:53,066 --> 00:05:59,212
So it starts in 1972, actually, and then it just falls in a line with more or less successful

109
00:05:59,252 --> 00:06:00,113
clones of other games.

