164
00:09:25,576 --> 00:09:29,498
people are going to hail you as a savior who's doing something not entirely new,

165
00:09:29,798 --> 00:09:34,321
but at least something that adds to an underserved audience and an underserved niche.

166
00:09:38,004 --> 00:09:41,127
So if you're going into, we're in these situations daily,

167
00:09:41,147 --> 00:09:42,769
you look at your game concept and say,

168
00:09:42,809 --> 00:09:44,992
okay, so what am I gonna do with my game?

169
00:09:45,112 --> 00:09:47,635
How much can I be inspired by other people?

170
00:09:48,116 --> 00:09:52,641
How do I need to work to make my game stand out?

171
00:09:53,142 --> 00:09:54,443
No matter the.

172
00:09:55,603 --> 00:09:59,405
actual gameplay value and the actual things you do in the game.

173
00:09:59,905 --> 00:10:03,706
And that's where I come in typically because we work a lot of paradox with

174
00:10:04,507 --> 00:10:08,769
