00:48:16,503 --> 00:48:17,523
than you can actually deliver.

864
00:48:18,539 --> 00:48:20,240
And trying to match the player fantasy

865
00:48:20,420 --> 00:48:21,561
with what you actually deliver,

866
00:48:21,582 --> 00:48:23,523
or even exceed the player fantasy,

867
00:48:23,924 --> 00:48:25,085
is a very hard balance as well.

868
00:48:26,606 --> 00:48:29,069
What is our commitment to deliver that?

869
00:48:33,073 --> 00:48:35,095
And I was mentioning Neyman Brands.

870
00:48:36,036 --> 00:48:36,776
Another part of that.

871
00:48:37,965 --> 00:48:44,049
They can use just as a toy of like coming up with what is actually unique about this game,

872
00:48:44,089 --> 00:48:47,612
what makes it stand out, are a few things like in sales,

873
00:48:47,632 --> 00:48:51,615
you often use an elevator pitch, which means that if you go up from elevator

874
00:48:51,635 --> 00:48:54,457
from floor 1 to floor 50, and you have to explain

875
00:48:54,498 --> 00:48:58,140
to a big-time CEO your business model, how does that sound?

876
00:48:58,240 --> 00:48:59,321
Because you only have 20 seconds.

877
00:48:59,862 --> 00:49:00,582
Same with your game.

