00:49:51,412 --> 00:49:55,794
What are the numbers? The most common numbers are, for example, a Metacritic score.

891
00:49:56,335 --> 00:49:59,236
The Metacritic score doesn't say that much, to be honest, about the game.

892
00:49:59,656 --> 00:50:05,099
Probably the user score in Metacritic says more about your game than the actual Metacritic score does.

893
00:50:05,819 --> 00:50:09,760
But you check out how long are your average player's sessions,

894
00:50:10,521 --> 00:50:14,682
and does that match up with how you thought that people would play the game?

895
00:50:14,982 --> 00:50:18,423
Did you think that people would play the game for one hour at a time,

